==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outgrow
<hw>Out*grow"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Outgrew</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Outgrown</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Outgrowing</conjf>.]</vmorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To surpass in growing; to grow more than.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To grow out of or away from; to grow too large, or
too aged, for; <as>as, to <ex>outgrow</ex> clothing; to <ex>outgrow</ex>
usefulness; to <ex>outgrow</ex> an infirmity.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outgrowth</ent>⟦br⟧
